While speaking on “rethinking development in Africa”, the CEO of African Union Development Agency – NEPAD noted that the critical transitions that are taking place on the continent include demographic, technological, natural systems, climate change, governance systems as well as human development transitions.  He alluded that none of these transitions can be dealt with independently. Mohamed Abdisalam, Head of Environmental Sustainability at AUDA-NEPAD joins CNBC Africa to discuss how policymakers on the continent should plan for the future of Africa’s development....